<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="673" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3172a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-28T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            28, 1920—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>397. A press item under Peking headline December 1st says Chinese
                                Ministry of Finance has sanctioned cancellation previous order
                                repudiating German section of Hukuang loan bonds and agreed that
                                these bonds will be honored when it is shown they do not possess
                                enemy character in the transaction.</p>
                            <p>Please verify and report by telegraph.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>